Will/Won't be able to

You can use will/won't be able to show that you have (or don't have) the ability to do womething in the future.
A verb follows able to.

I'll be able to finish the report by Friday. 
(I can finish the report by friday)

He won't be able to meet you after work.
(He can't meet you after work)

Will you able to do the work? 
Yes, I will.
No, I won't.

What will you able to complete by Friday?

I'll be able to complete the first part of the report.

